review_blob: In the way of pumpkin beers, this is the least favorite one I hav ever tasted. Way too spicy and pumpkin-y.
Double IPA that gives Pliny the Elder a serious run for its money. Super smooth. Light. Extraordinarily drinkable. One of my favorites.
This is simply the best porter I've very tasted. Delicious. Smoky. Smooth.
Not sure if I have tasted anything like this. Completely unique. Not highly drinkable but just so unique.
beer_name: Odell Mountain Standard Double Black IPA

review_blob: One of the best double IPAs out there. Smooth. Light. Little to no bitterness at the end. Highly drinkable. A lot like Flying Fish Exit 16.
